cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves learning a latent space that preserves semantic relationships between labels, which is a common theme in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve benchmark datasets that are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
